japan and thailand to jointli extract rare metal japan 's agenc of natur resourc and energi said it will begin experi with thailand at the end of march to start commerci product of rare metal in 1989 under a joint project . an agenc offici said it will set up a 500 mln yen pilot plant in bangkok which will extract high qualiti rare metal such as titanium and niobium from sand left over from tin product process in thailand . the plant wilq use about a tonn of sand per day , although it is unclear how much rare metal will be extract , the offici said .